history.content: That will be fine as long as you recognize it will be a lot of work and don't add too much time consuming stuff on top

children.subject: I took both together as a sophomore as well in the Spring and it was very manageable. But take this with a slight grain of salt.

history.content: For context, I'm a sophomore that will have finished 61ABC, 16AB, 70, and 170 after this semester. I want to take CS 162 next semester with a group of friends, and either 126 or 127 to start preparing for 189. Right now I'm leaning towards 126; would this schedule be too challenging for the Spring? Since one is a project class and another is a problem set class, it seems "balanced" in that regard. However, I know both classes take a lot, lot, lot of work. Should I consider some other schedule?
history.subject: 162 and 126 next Spring?
